Morphology . Head vertex slightly concave (
Fig. 15
). Hypandrium symmetrical (
Fig. 16
), with two acuminate projections on each postero–lateral corner, the outer one stouter; a mid, setose, stout posterior process, with sides coarsely serrate. Anterior hypandrium projections slender; posterior projections thick. Setae scattered in central zone of the hypandrium. Forewing venation (
Fig. 17
). Paraprocts elongate, outer border with a pigmented band and a distal spine–like projection; setae as illustrated, sensory fields with 36 trichobotria in basal rosettes. Epiproct almost trapeziform, slightly rounded posteriorly and concave near clunium; setae as illustrated (
Fig. 21
). Phallosome (
Fig. 20
) elongate, V–shaped, each side strut distally with an inwardly directed, wide based, pointed process. External parameres distally dilated, pointing outwards, bearing a field of short spines. Aedeagus long, slender, slightly curved proximally, each arm terminating in a field of short spines.
